title: Highest and Lowest Average Sunshine Amount, United States, 2008
name: Highest and Lowest Average Sunshine Amount, United States, 2008
description: This dataset illustrates the highest and lowest average sunshine amount for cities with 50,000 people or more.  A value of -1 means that the data was not applicable.  Also included are the rankings, the inverse ranking to be used for mapping purposes only, the population, and percent of average sunshine.Source: City-DataURL:  http://www.city-data.com/top2/c474.htmlhttp://www.city-data.com/top2/c475.htmlDate Accessed: November 12, 2007
